[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":585},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F28\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F28\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F28\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F28\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners\u002F":561,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F28\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners\u002F":570},"\u002Fother\u002F20190828\u002F2944044939\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":544,"date":545,"description":546,"extension":547,"lang":548,"meta":549,"navigation":550,"path":551,"readingMinutes":552,"seo":553,"standalone":554,"stem":555,"tags":556,"tldr":558,"updated":558,"url":559,"__hash__":560},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners.md","Slack Basics for Beginners","4944094493",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":517},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,30,33,36,40,43,46,52,55,61,64,70,73,79,82,88,92,95,100,108,119,122,147,150,156,159,165,172,177,180,186,189,195,198,204,210,213,216,222,226,229,234,237,252,255,260,263,269,273,280,285,290,294,297,301,304,309,313,316,322,328,331,335,339,346,352,355,361,365,368,374,378,381,387,390,396,400,407,413,417,420,426,429,432,440,445,451,459,464,470,474,477,483,489,493,500,507,511,514],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"A walkthrough of basic Slack — slightly long, but Slack is one of the most common team communication tools, so worth knowing.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"slack","Slack",[17,25,26],{},[27,28],"img",{"alt":23,"src":29},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FCN6Qmt2.png",[17,31,32],{},"Slack is a team communication tool — similar to LINE or WhatsApp in concept, but built for team workflows. You can delete sent messages, edit sent messages, organize conversations into topic channels and threads.",[17,34,35],{},"It supports team-wide workspaces with sub-channels and private channels. Slack is free for most personal\u002Fsmall-team use, and many companies adopt it as their internal communication tool.",[12,37,39],{"id":38},"joining-slack","Joining Slack",[17,41,42],{},"You can create your own workspace or join an existing one. Here I'll use an existing workspace as an example.",[17,44,45],{},"Typically someone shares an invite link. Click it and you get a screen asking for your email — to check if you have a Slack account:",[17,47,48],{},[27,49],{"alt":50,"src":51},"Sign up or join","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbLxjkiL.png",[17,53,54],{},"If you already have a Slack account, you'll join directly. First-time users get a verification email:",[17,56,57],{},[27,58],{"alt":59,"src":60},"First-time signup","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F04qmi0E.png",[17,62,63],{},"Click through to verify:",[17,65,66],{},[27,67],{"alt":68,"src":69},"Confirm email","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F3bLa5Ek.png",[17,71,72],{},"Then Slack asks for your name and password — these will be your default identity for any future Slack workspace (your email becomes your login):",[17,74,75],{},[27,76],{"alt":77,"src":78},"Account details","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FRVYLaiX.png",[17,80,81],{},"After that you're in:",[17,83,84],{},[27,85],{"alt":86,"src":87},"Web Slack","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FD0T6T752.png",[12,89,91],{"id":90},"installing-the-desktop-app","Installing the desktop app",[17,93,94],{},"I'd recommend installing the Slack desktop client. Without it, web-only Slack means you'll miss messages frequently.",[17,96,97],{},[27,98],{"alt":86,"src":99},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FWqF6Q0c.png",[17,101,102,103,107],{},"Slack's own banner at the top often says: ",[104,105,106],"code",{},"We strongly recommend enabling desktop notifications if you'll be using Slack on this computer."," Enable them.",[17,109,110,111,118],{},"Better — install the actual desktop app. Download page: ",[112,113,117],"a",{"href":114,"rel":115},"https:\u002F\u002Fslack.com\u002Fdownloads\u002F",[116],"nofollow","Download Slack",".",[17,120,121],{},"Direct links:",[123,124,125,133,140],"ul",{},[126,127,128],"li",{},[112,129,132],{"href":130,"rel":131},"https:\u002F\u002Fslack.com\u002Fdownloads\u002Fwindows",[116],"Windows",[126,134,135],{},[112,136,139],{"href":137,"rel":138},"https:\u002F\u002Fslack.com\u002Fdownloads\u002Fmac",[116],"Mac",[126,141,142],{},[112,143,146],{"href":144,"rel":145},"https:\u002F\u002Fslack.com\u002Fdownloads\u002Flinux",[116],"Linux",[17,148,149],{},"After installing, opening the app gives you a blank login screen:",[17,151,152],{},[27,153],{"alt":154,"src":155},"Initial screen","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FYWzDFZv.png",[17,157,158],{},"Click \"Sign In\" and a browser window opens asking for the workspace URL:",[17,160,161],{},[27,162],{"alt":163,"src":164},"Workspace URL","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FOCaPtfw.png",[17,166,167,168,171],{},"That URL slug is the workspace identifier (from when you joined — e.g., ",[104,169,170],{},"playSlackYa","):",[17,173,174],{},[27,175],{"alt":170,"src":176},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FRvWKwM2.png",[17,178,179],{},"Type it in:",[17,181,182],{},[27,183],{"alt":184,"src":185},"Workspace input","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FEtctOXD.png",[17,187,188],{},"Then you'll be redirected to log in:",[17,190,191],{},[27,192],{"alt":193,"src":194},"Login","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXvDUPUb.png",[17,196,197],{},"After login you might end up in web Slack (not sure why Slack does this). Back to the desktop app, click \"Sign In\" again — now you'll see the workspace in the top-left. Click into it and you're done:",[17,199,200],{},[27,201],{"alt":202,"src":203},"Slack app","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FJC7p1MZ.png",[17,205,206],{},[27,207],{"alt":208,"src":209},"Joined","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FtQyqlWv.png",[17,211,212],{},"A bit clunky the first time, but you only do it once per workspace.",[17,214,215],{},"To add another workspace later, click the menu in the top-left → Window → \"Sign in to Another Workspace\" and repeat:",[17,217,218],{},[27,219],{"alt":220,"src":221},"Add workspace","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGXSurPs.png",[12,223,225],{"id":224},"ui-tour","UI tour",[17,227,228],{},"Quick tour of the basic UI.",[230,231,233],"h3",{"id":232},"channels","Channels",[17,235,236],{},"Left sidebar shows channels. Two types:",[123,238,239,246],{},[126,240,241,245],{},[242,243,244],"strong",{},"Public channels"," — anyone can join",[126,247,248,251],{},[242,249,250],{},"Private channels"," — invite-only",[17,253,254],{},"Click any channel to switch and start chatting (or just lurking):",[17,256,257],{},[27,258],{"alt":233,"src":259},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F4GdFQri.png",[17,261,262],{},"To join an existing public channel, click \"Add a channel\". You can also create your own:",[17,264,265],{},[27,266],{"alt":267,"src":268},"Add a channel","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fv6hOh1O.png",[230,270,272],{"id":271},"direct-messages","Direct Messages",[17,274,275,276,279],{},"1-on-1 DMs. If the person isn't already in your DM list, click the ",[104,277,278],{},"+"," to add them:",[17,281,282],{},[27,283],{"alt":272,"src":284},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPJ40DsC.png",[17,286,287],{},[27,288],{"alt":272,"src":289},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXbleHvk.png",[230,291,293],{"id":292},"apps","Apps",[17,295,296],{},"Slack supports many integrations to speed up workflows. I haven't used much, so skipping.",[230,298,300],{"id":299},"threads","Threads",[17,302,303],{},"Threads are one of my favorite features — focus a follow-up discussion on a specific message instead of derailing the channel:",[17,305,306],{},[27,307],{"alt":300,"src":308},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FjOmY5wp.png",[230,310,312],{"id":311},"muting-a-channel","Muting a channel",[17,314,315],{},"For chatter channels you don't need to follow live, mute notifications via the gear icon → \"Mute xxx\":",[17,317,318],{},[27,319],{"alt":320,"src":321},"Mute","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FuxjgQPS.png",[17,323,324],{},[27,325],{"alt":326,"src":327},"Muted bell icon","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FlWuXzFO.png",[17,329,330],{},"Slack also automatically silences notifications at certain hours (super useful).",[12,332,334],{"id":333},"common-features","Common features",[230,336,338],{"id":337},"editing-messages","Editing messages",[17,340,341,342,345],{},"Send a message, realize it was wrong — hover, click ",[104,343,344],{},"..."," → Edit:",[17,347,348],{},[27,349],{"alt":350,"src":351},"Edit","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FAEsWoVj.png",[17,353,354],{},"Or press the up arrow key to jump straight to editing your last message:",[17,356,357],{},[27,358],{"alt":359,"src":360},"Edit via arrow","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FEGPnYJi.png",[230,362,364],{"id":363},"deleting-messages","Deleting messages",[17,366,367],{},"Same pattern as editing. Deleted messages are gone from the recipient's view:",[17,369,370],{},[27,371],{"alt":372,"src":373},"Delete","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FgLoSZjL.png",[230,375,377],{"id":376},"threading","Threading",[17,379,380],{},"Hover a message and \"Start a thread\" appears:",[17,382,383],{},[27,384],{"alt":385,"src":386},"Start a thread","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVaqWRFr.png",[17,388,389],{},"Replies in the thread don't clutter the main channel — Slack notifies you of new thread replies:",[17,391,392],{},[27,393],{"alt":394,"src":395},"Thread","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FlmfnaAH.png",[230,397,399],{"id":398},"tagging","Tagging",[17,401,402,403,406],{},"Like LINE\u002FFacebook — ",[104,404,405],{},"@name"," to tag someone. They get notified:",[17,408,409],{},[27,410],{"alt":411,"src":412},"Tag","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FxGEq9a9.png",[230,414,416],{"id":415},"emoji-reactions","Emoji reactions",[17,418,419],{},"Beyond emojis in messages, you can react with an emoji to someone else's message:",[17,421,422],{},[27,423],{"alt":424,"src":425},"Reactions","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqoXw3NV.png",[230,427,428],{"id":104},"Code",[17,430,431],{},"Slack supports both inline code and code blocks:",[123,433,434],{},[126,435,436,439],{},[242,437,438],{},"Inline code"," — wrap text in single backticks",[17,441,442],{},[27,443],{"alt":438,"src":444},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FxJhsOuj.png",[17,446,447],{},[27,448],{"alt":449,"src":450},"Inline code source","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FBh7pMbZ.png",[123,452,453],{},[126,454,455,458],{},[242,456,457],{},"Code block"," — wrap text in triple backticks",[17,460,461],{},[27,462],{"alt":457,"src":463},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FlyXegev.png",[17,465,466],{},[27,467],{"alt":468,"src":469},"Code block source","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fzoopoeo.png",[230,471,473],{"id":472},"markdown","Markdown",[17,475,476],{},"Slack supports basic Markdown — once you know Markdown, you've got Slack:",[17,478,479],{},[27,480],{"alt":481,"src":482},"Common Markdown","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FV94KGsu.png",[17,484,485],{},[27,486],{"alt":487,"src":488},"Markdown rendering","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F9I2XxY4.png",[230,490,492],{"id":491},"other","Other",[17,494,495,496,499],{},"Slack has lots more — drag and drop files, ",[104,497,498],{},"Ctrl + V"," to paste screenshots, etc. Too many to cover.",[17,501,502,503,118],{},"To change Slack's UI language, see ",[112,504,506],{"href":505},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F04\u002F08\u002Fchange-slack-ui-language\u002F","How to Change Slack's UI Language",[12,508,510],{"id":509},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[17,512,513],{},"That's most of the day-to-day Slack basics. Not hard, and honestly Slack makes code-related chat way better than LINE — in LINE you'll watch your code message get buried by chit-chat within seconds. Slack's threads avoid that.",[17,515,516],{},"Thanks to Yeh for opening a Slack workspace for me to screenshot.",{"title":518,"searchDepth":519,"depth":519,"links":520},"",2,[521,522,523,524,525,533,543],{"id":14,"depth":519,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":519,"text":23},{"id":38,"depth":519,"text":39},{"id":90,"depth":519,"text":91},{"id":224,"depth":519,"text":225,"children":526},[527,529,530,531,532],{"id":232,"depth":528,"text":233},3,{"id":271,"depth":528,"text":272},{"id":292,"depth":528,"text":293},{"id":299,"depth":528,"text":300},{"id":311,"depth":528,"text":312},{"id":333,"depth":519,"text":334,"children":534},[535,536,537,538,539,540,541,542],{"id":337,"depth":528,"text":338},{"id":363,"depth":528,"text":364},{"id":376,"depth":528,"text":377},{"id":398,"depth":528,"text":399},{"id":415,"depth":528,"text":416},{"id":104,"depth":528,"text":428},{"id":472,"depth":528,"text":473},{"id":491,"depth":528,"text":492},{"id":509,"depth":519,"text":510},"Misc","2019-08-28 08:52:12","A walkthrough of Slack basics — how to join a Slack workspace, download the desktop client, navigate the UI (channels, direct messages, threads), and the everyday features you'll actually use (editing\u002Fdeleting messages, threading, tagging, emoji reactions, code blocks, Markdown). For anyone joining a team that uses Slack for the first time.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners","4",{"title":6,"description":546},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners",[23,557],"Software",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F28\u002Fslack-basics-for-beginners\u002F","1g1YCowXRf8sFzsKNvcbISdetLeVGMxVzpt0jv7FAPs",{"newer":562,"older":566},{"url":563,"title":564,"date":565},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F02\u002Fthinkphp-day-01-intro\u002F","Day 1 - Learning ThinkPHP From Scratch: An Introduction","2019-09-02 11:28:58",{"url":567,"title":568,"date":569},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F21\u002Fnuxt-window-or-document-undefined-fix\u002F","Fixing 'window or document undefined' in Nuxt","2019-08-21 11:23:55",[571,576,581],{"url":572,"title":573,"date":574,"readingMinutes":575},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":577,"title":578,"date":579,"readingMinutes":580},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":582,"title":583,"date":584,"readingMinutes":552},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00",1784012780067]